t has reached out to the overseas community. We also have a lot of supports from overseas.  Therefore we will maintain our focus on the overseas market. The testnet of Nebulas NOVA has already been released, and in our market plan of 2019, we will put more attention on the overseas market, including delivering more PR articles and also paying more attention on developers community. We will also try to apply ATP on-chain advertisement to better improve the performance of our overseas market and operation.</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'108.162.245.67',0,1),(167,20,33,'2019-01-11 04:45:14',136,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"20\" displayname=\"Mista-Mist\" id=\"148\" number=\"15\" username=\"Mista-Mist\">@Mista-Mist#148</POSTMENTION> Thanks for your questions. We have put in extensive efforts on the research and development of the underlying infrastructure of Nebulas, and it does not mean that we pay less attention in building the ecosystem or marketing.</p>\n\n<p>As a public chain project, we have always been holding strong with respect to the market, and it<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s hard for any single project to beat the entire market condition. Nebulas keeps forging ahead to complete our promises and goals, and we hope our community could join us together to make Nebulas better.</p>\n\n<p>In terms of our ecosystem development, our key target is to introduce incremental token users to our ecosystem and thus to create a sustainable and sound ecosystem. We have incubated the first benchmark protocol layer application Atlas Protocol and as a on-chain advertising protocol, Atlas is not just an application of Nebulas mainnet, it also supports the marketing and user adoption- not only Nebulas and our ecosystem, but also the entire blockchain industry.  Meanwhile, I personally have initiated Bitsclub Vision Program and the Public Chain Technology Alliance (PTCA) which already has over 20 partners in the entire public chain ecosystem. We hope that within PCTA, thes