 ensures that funding is captured and allocated to new development projects for Nebulas. The most direct way is a treasury function with proper governance to ensure effective allocation (seems most appropriate here), secondly it could be services to third parties from the Nebulas team (seems less likely).</p>\n\n<p>Can you elaborate on your plans for the long-term funding beyond the ICO proceeds?</p>\n\n<p>Thanks</p></t>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.134.223',0,1),(316,67,1,'2019-02-12 08:44:25',31,'comment','<r><p>It<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s time to talk about Blockchain governance.<br/>\nIf you have some ideas and suggestions about Blockchain Governance, you can discuss it here.</p>\n\n<p>Governance in blockchains can be broadly separated into 2 primary categories:<br/>\n1 Off-Chain Governance<br/>\n2 On-Chain Governance</p>\n\n<p>Some posts about blockchain governance:<br/>\n<URL url=\"https://blockonomi.com/blockchain-governance/\"><s>[</s>What is Blockchain Governance? Complete Beginners Guide<e>](https://blockonomi.com/blockchain-governance/)</e></URL><br/>\n<URL url=\"https://blog.goodaudience.com/blockchain-governance-101-eea5201d7992\"><s>[</s>Blockchain Governance 101<e>](https://blog.goodaudience.com/blockchain-governance-101-eea5201d7992)</e></URL></p>\n\n\n<p>When NOVA on Mainnet in April, every time the parameters of DIP will be changed, everyone should have chances to discuss it. It should be open.</p>\n\n<p>So there are some questions:</p>\n\n<LIST><LI><s>- </s>What do you think about the future of DIP?</LI>\n<LI><s>- </s>Should we have special On-Chain Governance? Because of NR, DIP.</LI>\n<LI><s>- </s>Any proposals about On-Chain Governance?</LI>\n<LI><s>- </s>Should we open more non-tech bounties?</LI></LIST>\n\n<p>It<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s your turn!</p>\n</r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.78.97',0,1),(317,49,4,'2019-02-12 08:45:32',31,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"49\" displayname=\"starkstay\" id=\"313\" number=\"3\" username=\"starkstay\">@starkstay#313</POSTMENTION> Have you leave your email?</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.78.97',0,1),(318,66,2,'2019-02-12 09:00:38',31,'comment','<r><p>Thank you for your support.<br/>\nAnd there is a plan for Blockchain governance. If we want to build a self-evolving ecosystem, then consensus and incentive are more important.<br/>\nWe want to hear your voices. You can leave your suggestions <URL url=\"https://community.nebulas.io/d/67-about-blockchain-governance\"><s>[</s>here<e>](https://community.nebulas.io/d/67-about-blockchain-governance)</e></URL>.</p> </r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.78.73',0,1),(319,67,2,'2019-02-12 18:19:31',178,'comment','<t><p>One of my main questions to the Nebulas team and the community is how the long term funding of Nebulas is secured / built into the NAS eco-system to ensure an ongoing development of platform / NAS infrastructure.</p>\n\n<p>I am thinking beyond the ICO proceeds / tokens.</p>\n\n<p>Other blockchain like EOS, DASH, Decred have build in treaures where part of the transaction fee is allocated to fund new projects.</p>\n\n<p>I am aware of the DIP mechanism, but as I understand it, it only concerns new DApps and also is limited to the distribution of 35% if the total token supply so eventually it will run out.</p>\n\n<p>What is Nebulas long term plan in this respect?</p>\n\n<p>Thanks.</p></t>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.134.31',0,1),(320,49,5,'2019-02-12 18:31:01',131,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"49\" displayname=\"smalloranges\" id=\"317\" number=\"4\" username=\"smalloranges\">@smalloranges#317</POSTMENTION> yes I left it as directed on the other thread. Not a huge thing but couldn<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t find a follow up in my email.</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'172.69.70.236',0,1),(321,68,1,'2019-02-12 20:22:44',179,'comment','<r><p>Hello everyone, I<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>m a new member, at community.nebulas.io. I don<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t know about nebulas.io. I just learned it little by little, asking for instructions from friends! thank you, thank you</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'172.69.134.132',0,1),(322,67,3,'2019-02-12 22:51:52',127,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"67\" displayname=\"SrColumbus\" id=\"319\" number=\"2\" username=\"SrColumbus\">@SrColumbus#319</POSTMENTION> <br/>\nYou make a good point and it may be something work considering. Since Nebulas went live, they have been holding the DPoS minted coins as a community fund. Perhaps this will be future development funding once development gets more decentralized and passed over to the Nebulas community - and at some point, this must happen for Nebulas to be successful.</p>\n\n<p>I do like Decred<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s governance and voting system. A few months ago, they even released the funds to the community to decide what to do with them and vote via the built in voting system. <br/>\nLook at other projects such as BTC, LTC, XMR, and even ETH - none of them have a funding built into the consensus system. They rely on community development and funding from the community &amp; creators albeit, ETH raised money for development.</p> </r>','2019-02-12 22:53:16',127,NULL,NULL,'172.69.42.79',0,1),(323,67,4,'2019-02-13 04:12:32',152,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"67\" displayname=\"SrColumbus\" id=\"319\" number=\"2\" username=\"SrColumbus\">@SrColumbus#319</POSTMENTION> <br/>\nmakes a good point given also that during the first DIP in mid-2018 the team was too generous with their rewards in NAS to dapp developers. Aside from the 35% allocated to NR &amp; DIP, as per whitepaper there is also a yearly inflation of 3-4% of the total supply allocated to incentivizing developers, if necessary. Let<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s hope it doesn<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t happen too often given that if the price per token doesn<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t appreciate, than devs won<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t see NAS as a good incentive to remain part of the ecosystem. Though I don<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t see how beneficial it would be to keep on flooding the market with NAS to cover incentives. I believe that is the wrong approach. I am currently witnessing it with the project AION Network where they are hyper-inflating their circulating supply with tokens but yet are not doing anything what so ever to stimulate community interest to improve market performance. Nebulas is a project i love very much and i believe their idea of having created Nebulas Rank and incentivizing developers is the perfect strategy for writing quality code and potentially developing killer apps. But Nebulas does worry me a bit lately. I do not see much community interest around the project as of late. The non-Chinese social media channels and chatrooms are extremely quiet. Barely interaction at all. Not much on Reddit or Twitter. Given that i haven<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t looked at Chinese social media channels, i do hope there is far more activity there to stimulate growth and interest around Nebulas for when NOVA mainnet is released. Because as it stands i really don<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t see how they will succeed at transitioning from a corporate structure to a communitized structure. I<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>m sure the team isn<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t oblivious to the current situation around the project and im sure there is a plan in place, but sadly it will take a lot more than Twitter and this forum to push for adoption and to have the platform stress-tested by a big community.<br/>\nSomething i am very curious about is in early 2018 when the Nebulas team was doing plenty of meetups and events in major cities, it seemed like attendance was very packed. I wonder if it was because of Edith Yung as an advisor to the project, but clearly a good PR and marketing push would do wonders for Nebulas because this lack of noise doesnt do Nebulas justice presently.</p> </r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'173.245.52.142',0,1),(324,68,2,'2019-02-13 04:46:59',31,'discussionTagged','[[1],[4]]',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,1),(325,68,3,'2019-02-13 04:47:34',31,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"68\" displayname=\"ken72\" id=\"321\" number=\"1\" username=\"ken72\">@ken72#321</POSTMENTION> Hello. I changed the tag #news &amp; announcements to #beginners. &#128512;</p> </r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.78.73',0,1),(326,68,4,'2019-02-13 04:51:54',31,'comment','<r><p>About <URL url=\"https://nebulas.io/technology.html\"><s>[</s>Nebulas Technology<e>](https://nebulas.io/technology.html)</e></URL><br/>\nAbout the current version mainnet: <URL url=\"https://nebulas.io/nova.html\"><s>[</s>Nebulas NOVA<e>](https://nebulas.io/nova.html)</e></URL><br/>\n<URL url=\"https://nebulas.io/nas.html\"><s>[</s>Get NAS<e>](https://nebulas.io/nas.html)</e></URL> &amp; <URL url=\"https://nebulas.io/wallets.html\"><s>[</s>hold NAS<e>](https://nebulas.io/wallets.html)</e></URL>.</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.78.73',0,1),(327,49,6,'2019-02-13 05:47:11',84,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"49\" displayname=\"starkstay\" id=\"320\" number=\"5\" username=\"starkstay\">@starkstay#320</POSTMENTION> Please stay tuned, we will solve this problem as soon as possible.</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'108.162.246.38',0,1),(328,67,5,'2019-02-13 10:53:10',151,'comment','<r><p>I guess the team just chose the wrong strategy at this moment. They think that by creating a good technology popularity of the project will rise, but that<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s not true in my opinion The current Dev Incentive season need to be marketized in a better way, it needs more devs to be attracted. BTW suddenly today the TX amount in testnet dropped greatly, as if all thoose smartcontracts just evaporated. What caused this? Also blockchain needs adoption in a general way. Maybe Nebulas can be one of the first to do this. It needs to be more intuitive. <URL url=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sUCpuaqlISQ\"><s>[</s><FP char=\"\">\"</FP>Technology alone is not enough<FP char=\"\">\"</FP><e>](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sUCpuaqlISQ)</e></URL> Steve Jobs</p></r>','2019-02-13 10:54:03',151,NULL,NULL,'172.69.10.175',0,1),(329,67,6,'2019-02-13 12:47:55',31,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"67\" displayname=\"Mista-Mist\" id=\"323\" number=\"4\" username=\"Mista-Mist\">@Mista-Mist#323</POSTMENTION> Thank you for your support.<br/>\nYou are right, through the changing of the price, Nebulas is not as popular as before. Complicated reasons. DIP is still on testnet, under testing. Many people can<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t feel it now. With special tech features, there will be a chance to build a better voting system and on-chain governance. I think it<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s just the beginning. If we solve a real problem, there will be something happened.<br/>\nIf you have any suggestion, please tell us. Tell everyone in the community, not only the team members.<br/>\nThank you again.</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.106.87',0,1),(330,67,7,'2019-02-13 13:42:34',31,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"67\" displayname=\"Peacemaker\" id=\"328\" number=\"5\" username=\"Peacemaker\">@Peacemaker#328</POSTMENTION> Here: <URL url=\"https://explorer.nebulas.io/#/testnet/dip-leaderboard?p=1\"><s>[</s>The DIP awards<e>](https://explorer.nebulas.io/#/testnet/dip-leaderboard?p=1)</e></URL>.<br/>\nIt<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s testnet. Not mainnet. There isn<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t a lot of data. And it<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s Chinese spring festival last week. All Chinese developers went home with their families. So<FP char=\"\">...</FP><FP char=\"\">...</FP> &gt;_&lt;</p> \n\n<p>And I am so glad that you are talking about the problems. What do you think is more important? For example, Off-Chain Governance? Non-tech bounties?</p>\n\n<p>What I think is that we should give people a reason to use Nebulas.<br/>\n1 It<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s easy to use, developers can use Nebulas to build a better DApps or even kill DApps. Then many users can use these DApps. You know, Nebulas is a public blockchain. Common people won<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t use it directly. It isn<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t a wallet, Steemit<FP char=\"\">...</FP><FP char=\"\">...</FP> Not applications. Different. <br/>\n2 With hopes. Nebulas is an ecosystem. People can get benefits without developing DApps. Developers are just a part of the community, not all. People can use it, hold NAS, make friends, do many things.<br/>\nNow I guess many people don<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t understand what<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s autonomous metanet and why we want to build this ecosystem. &#128514; A lot of works to do.</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.106.201',0,1),(331,67,8,'2019-02-13 15:02:52',152,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"67\" displayname=\"smalloranges\" id=\"330\" number=\"7\" username=\"smalloranges\">@smalloranges#330</POSTMENTION> I agree with your description of a public chain. Many other blockchains are public too like Tron, Zilliqa, EOS, EThereum, and eventually all those blockchains will be so busy and used that they will all become autonomous. But while the project is being governed by a corporation, it should be the goal of the corporation to increase awareness and PR, and have a marketing campaign around the project, so that once it is fully in the spotlight, than the governing body can take a step back gradually and give more power to the community. Kind of like Decred has done. <br/>\nIt<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s important to know also that the crypto space and blockchain industry was a place for cypherpunks and geeks in the early early days, but it is not the case anymore. It is now being run by corporations, venture capitalists, entrepreneurs seeking to generate profits, business minded people. Even developers who have great ideas for dapps look for the platform that will generate them the most profit and will give the most exposure to their dapp. I believe that was the ultimate goal of Da Hongfei as a business person when he transitioned from Antshares to NEO, all those business strategies he applied made NEO very popular, and despite their tech issues they still have communities of developers in geographical locations developing big dapps, DEX<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s, virtual machines for dapps, etc<FP char=\"\">...</FP>.So possibly when Testnet is complete and mainnet is live, we should have a strong marketing campaign with the help of big names, similar to Edith Yung in the early nebulas days, to help give us a nice boost.</p> </r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.62.54',0,1),(332,67,9,'2019-02-13 19:01:41',151,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"67\" displayname=\"smalloranges\" id=\"330\" number=\"7\" username=\"smalloranges\">@smalloranges#330</POSTMENTION></p> \n\n<QUOTE><i>&gt; </i><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"67\" displayname=\"smalloranges\" id=\"330\" number=\"7\" username=\"smalloranges\">@smalloranges#330</POSTMENTION> Now I guess many people dont understand whats autonomous metanet and why we want to build this ecosystem.<br/>\n<i>&gt; </i>We don<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t know much right now about autonomous metanet. It would be great to have some new info about it.</p></QUOTE>\n\n<p>The most important thing at this moment is to have more developers , creating new stuff on NAS blockchain. By the time testnet incentive program ends there should be some good dapps(at least 2 - 3 of them) We just need more people somehow to be attracted, Nebulas has such a unique DIP feature which no other blockchain has, This feature should be spreaded. We already have some of NAS tech functioning, this is great and I think it<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s time to slowly show up on this scene. But thats just my opinion</p></r>','2019-02-13 19:03:29',151,NULL,NULL,'172.69.10.97',0,1),(333,69,1,'2019-02-14 04:41:33',180,'comment','<r><p>Neber.io<br/>\n()()<br/>\nDApp</p>\n\n<p><br/>\n    </p>\n<LIST><LI><s>- </s>()</LI>\n<LI><s>- </s>(DApp)</LI></LIST>\n\n<p></p>\n<LIST><LI><s>- </s> Keystore</LI>\n<LI><s>- </s></LI>\n<LI><s>- </s></LI>\