 on how to follow-up with the winning dApps to ensure that they keep improving the dApps in cooperation with Nebulas and the community </LI>\n<LI><s>- </s>Keep improving Nebulas with the current ICO funds where community engagement and involvement should play an important role (I guess cross-chain functionality to leverage on other blockchains growth and adoption should play a key role. If Nebulas dApps could use Bitcoin, Ethereum, EOS, Tron and NEO etc. data / transactions as input to their dApps and engage with them through Nebulas and NR could take such data into consideration Nebulas could indeed take shape as the MetaNet intended) </LI>\n<LI><s>- </s>Once the DIP has proven itself successful, then determine how the long term funding of Nebulas / NAS eco-system will take place incl. the on-chain governance where I expect NR / token staking should play a role</LI>\n<LI><s>- </s>Identify where the key use cases are for short term adoption of Nebulas and market Nebulas to such communities (it could be the gaming industry as already mention by the Nebulas team, which is the area that typically is prone for early internet / technology adoption)</LI></LIST></r>','2019-02-14 19:18:11',178,NULL,NULL,'162.158.134.49',0,1),(345,70,1,'2019-02-14 18:44:10',152,'comment','<t><p>I know it has been repeated several times and I am sure the team is fully aware of it, but adding NAS onto the ledger NANO hardware device will surely bring a lot of exposure to Nebulas. It is indeed a good marketing strategy to be leveraged, given that the whole community in crypto waits every Tuesday of the month to see which coins are added onto the Ledger. The application has been submitted a long time ago, even when Robin Z was still part of the team. Hardware wallet is important for the security of the NAS holders as well as a good exposure/marketing strategy, letting everyone know that Nebulas is back!   Thanks</p>  </t>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.126.133',0,1),(346,70,2,'2019-02-15 09:12:31',31,'comment','<r><p>Now, there is a hardware wallet supporting NAS: <URL url=\"http://www.kisc.io/\"><s>[</s>Kaiser Wallet<e>](http://www.kisc.io/)</e></URL>. It<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s from Korea. So perhaps it<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s not easy to get it out of Asia.<br/>\nAnd the hardware wallet bounty is open again. <URL url=\"https://nebulas.io/developers.html\"><s>[</s>Here<e>](https://nebulas.io/developers.html)</e></URL>. Good news, some people already claimed it. Wait for good news. <br/>\nAnd welcome to dev more hardware wallet. Only one or two wallets are not enough. And welcome to recommend hardware wallets.</p> \n\n<p><URL url=\"https://nebulas.io/wallets.html\"><s>[</s>Click here<e>](https://nebulas.io/wallets.html)</e></URL> to see all wallets support NAS.</p>\n\n<p>Thank you for your support.</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.106.201',0,1),(347,71,1,'2019-02-15 09:31:48',31,'comment','<r><p><UPL-IMAGE-PREVIEW url=\"https://community.nebulas.io/assets/files/2019-02-15/1550222141-82189-2019-02-15-171512.png\">[upl-image-preview url=https://community.nebulas.io/assets/files/2019-02-15/1550222141-82189-2019-02-15-171512.png]</UPL-IMAGE-PREVIEW></p>\n\n<p>According to the <URL url=\"https://nebulas.io/roadmap.html\"><s>[</s>Nebulas core roadmap<e>](https://nebulas.io/roadmap.html)</e></URL> (above), the next version needs a name. You can post your idea below, and click <FP char=\"\">\"</FP>like<FP char=\"\">\"</FP> button to support the one you like.<br/>\nThe name should be:</p>\n\n<LIST type=\"decimal\"><LI><s>1. </s>About the universe. The first version is Eagle Nebula, because the Pillars of Creation, it<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s the beginning of a star. The second version is Nebulas NOVA.</LI>\n<LI><s>2. </s>The topic is <FP char=\"\">\"</FP>Change the Unchangeable<FP char=\"\">\"</FP>. Nebulas Force will be online in this version. It<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s a kind of new upgrade capabilities. we think self-evolution is the future of autonomy. Nebulas Force (NF) provides the ability to upgrade without hard forks. So the name should be not only a star, it can describe a whole picture of many objects.</LI>\n<LI><s>3. </s>Easy to remember. It shouldn<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t be too long or too complicated.</LI></LIST></r>','2019-02-15 09:32:03',31,NULL,NULL,'162.158.106.87',0,1),(348,71,2,'2019-02-15 09:34:30',31,'comment','<r><p>For example, COSMOS.<br/>\nThis word describes a whole picture of the universe, and <FP char=\"\">\"</FP>Using the word cosmos rather than the word universe implies viewing the universe as a complex and orderly system or entity<FP char=\"\">\"</FP>. It looks better.</p></r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'162.158.106.129',0,1),(349,71,3,'2019-02-15 09:50:09',112,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"71\" displayname=\"smalloranges\" id=\"348\" number=\"2\" username=\"smalloranges\">@smalloranges#348</POSTMENTION> COSMOS is the name of an existing project, something related to cross-chain, better have something related to the <FP char=\"\">\"</FP>change the unchangeable<FP char=\"\">\"</FP>?</p> </r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'103.22.200.207',0,1),(350,72,1,'2019-02-15 10:56:59',168,'comment','<r><QUOTE><i>&gt; </i><p> <br/>\n</p></QUOTE>\n\n<p>20081031Satoshi Nakamoto</p>\n\n<p>20176</p>\n\n<p>20181231Nebulas NOVANebulas NOVA</p>\n\n<p>Nebulas NOVA</p>\n\n<p><STRONG><s>**</s><e>**</e></STRONG></p>\n\n<H3><s>### </s></H3>\n<p></p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p>on-chainoff-chain</p>\n\n<p>off-chaintoken holder</p>\n\n<p>PoW1000EIPEIP</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n<p><STRONG><s>**</s>on-chain<e>**</e></STRONG></p>\n\n<p>token holder</p>\n\n<p>Nebulas NOVA</p>\n\n<H3><s>### </s>Nebulas NOVA</H3>\n<H3><s>### </s>Nebulas NOVA</H3>\n\n<p>2018Nebulas NOVA3Nebulas NOVA</p>\n\n<p>Nebulas NOVANebulas ForceNBRE</p>\n\n<p>NBRE</p>\n\n<p><STRONG><s>**</s>NBREtoken user<e>**</e></STRONG></p>\n\n<p><STRONG><s>**</s><e>**</e></STRONG></p>\n\n<p>PoWNebulas NOVANBRE</p>\n\n<p>off-chainon-chain</p>\n\n<p>::::::</p>\n</r>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'172.68.133.225',0,1),(351,67,13,'2019-02-15 11:02:58',31,'comment','<r><p><POSTMENTION discussionid=\"67\" displayname=\"SrColumbus\" id=\"344\" number=\"12\" username=\"SrColumbus\">@SrColumbus#344</POSTMENTION> I know that Chinese saying, . I agree with you. Without the real situation, we can<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t discuss on-chain governance or other things. And there are still some problems.</p>\n\n<LIST type=\"decimal\"><LI><s>1. </s>It<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s not easy to find the key use case. You can see uses cases on the <URL url=\"https://nebulas.io/index.html\"><s>[</s>homepage<e>](https://nebulas.io/index.html)</e></URL> (below), which will be the key use case? In fact, I don<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t know. People can do it together and I don<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t know who will get the key first. Perhaps it<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s better for Nebulas to build a better ecosystem to support these innovations.  </LI></LIST>\n\n<p><UPL-IMAGE-PREVIEW url=\"https://community.nebulas.io/assets/files/2019-02-15/1550226988-487048-2019-02-15-183614.png\">[upl-image-preview url=https://community.nebulas.io/assets/files/2019-02-15/1550226988-487048-2019-02-15-183614.png]</UPL-IMAGE-PREVIEW></p>\n\n\n<LIST start=\"2\" type=\"decimal\"><LI><s>2. </s><p>Review the Nebulas Incentive Program (Season 1). We not only try to help developers but also invite other people to join NIP. In the whole ecosystem, developers can be the first part of people to touch, but not all. So perhaps we can<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>t just do DIP testnet program only. It will be very hard to move that program. So what about starting non-tech bounties?</p></LI>\n\n<LI><s>3. </s><p>DIP, Developer Incentive Program, is a native part of on-chain governance. It<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s automatic. But how to change the parameters? How to let more people feel that they can take part in it and DIP is not built for one person, it<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s for everyone<FP char=\"\">\'</FP>s future?</p></LI></LIST>\n</r>',NULL,NULL,N